our_ext_is_parallax_mouse&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_infinite&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_fadeout_animation&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_mobile_static&quot;:&quot;false&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"nested-accordion.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-n-accordion\" aria-label=\"Accordion. Open links with Enter or Space, close with Escape, and navigate with Arrow Keys\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<details id=\"e-n-accordion-item-1140\" class=\"e-n-accordion-item\" >\n\t\t\t\t<summary class=\"e-n-accordion-item-title\" data-accordion-index=\"1\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-controls=\"e-n-accordion-item-1140\" >\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-header'><div class=\"e-n-accordion-item-title-text\"> Read <span class=\"read-more\">More<\/span><span class=\"read-less\">Less<\/span> <\/div><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-icon'>\n\t\t\t<span class='e-opened' ><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"e-font-icon-svg e-fas-long-arrow-alt-down\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\"><path d=\"M168 345.941V44c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12h-56c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12v301.941H41.941c-21.382 0-32.09 25.851-16.971 40.971l86.059 86.059c9.373 9.373 24.569 9.373 33.941 0l86.059-86.059c15.119-15.119 4.411-40.971-16.971-40.971H168z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span>\n\t\t\t<span class='e-closed'><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"e-font-icon-svg e-fas-long-arrow-alt-right\" viewBox=\"0 0 448 512\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\"><path d=\"M313.941 216H12c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12v56c0 6.627 5.373 12 12 12h301.941v46.059c0 21.382 25.851 32.09 40.971 16.971l86.059-86.059c9.373-9.373 9.373-24.569 0-33.941l-86.059-86.059c-15.119-15.119-40.971-4.411-40.971 16.971V216z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span>\n\t\t<\/span>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/summary>\n\t\t\t\t<div role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"e-n-accordion-item-1140\" class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-32f7ac4 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"32f7ac4\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_parallax&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_backdrop&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_on_scroll&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_sticky&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_scrollme&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_smoove&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_parallax_mouse&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_infinite&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_fadeout_animation&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_mobile_static&quot;:&quot;false&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2abe04e elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2abe04e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_sticky&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_scrollme&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_smoove&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_parallax_mouse&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_infinite&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_fadeout_animation&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_mobile_static&quot;:&quot;false&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p data-start=\"202\" data-end=\"606\"><strong data-start=\"202\" data-end=\"214\">Haridwar<\/strong><br data-start=\"214\" data-end=\"217\" \/>One of the oldest and most visited holy cities in India, Haridwar is where the Ganga enters the plains. The Ganga Aarti at Har Ki Pauri is the highlight, drawing pilgrims and travelers every evening. It\u2019s also a starting point for the Char Dham Yatra. With its temples, ghats, and constant hum of prayers, Haridwar offers a strong spiritual presence without needing much effort to find it.<\/p><p data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"955\"><strong data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"621\">Kedarnath<\/strong><br data-start=\"621\" data-end=\"624\" \/>Kedarnath is one of the most important Shiva temples in India, and part of the Char Dham circuit. Reaching it takes effort\u2014either a long uphill trek or a helicopter ride\u2014but the setting is unmatched. Surrounded by mountains and glaciers, the temple stands strong and simple. It\u2019s a place that many visit once, and remember forever.<\/p><p data-start=\"957\" data-end=\"1363\"><strong data-start=\"957\" data-end=\"970\">Badrinath<\/strong><br data-start=\"970\" data-end=\"973\" \/>Dedicated to Lord Vishnu, Badrinath is located along the Alaknanda River and is also part of the Char Dham. The temple is colourful and welcoming, and the surrounding mountains make it feel peaceful even when it\u2019s crowded. Many people combine it with a visit to Mana, the last village before the Indo-China border. It\u2019s easy to reach by road, and the drive itself is part of the experience.<\/p><p data-start=\"1365\" data-end=\"1753\"><strong data-start=\"1365\" data-end=\"1381\">Kainchi Dham<\/strong><br data-start=\"1381\" data-end=\"1384\" \/>Near Nainital, Kainchi Dham is a peaceful ashram dedicated to Neem Karoli Baba. It\u2019s not as big or busy as other places, but it\u2019s known for its quiet power. Many followers of Baba\u2014including well-known tech leaders\u2014have visited for peace and clarity. The ashram is simple, surrounded by trees and hills, and leaves a calm feeling even if you stay for just a short while.<\/p><p data-start=\"1755\" data-end=\"2172\"><strong data-start=\"1755\" data-end=\"1768\">Char Dham<\/strong><br data-start=\"1768\" data-end=\"1771\" \/>The full Char Dham Yatra includes Yamunotri, Gangotri, Kedarnath, and Badrinath. It\u2019s one of the most important pilgrimages in Hindu tradition. The journey takes you deep into the Himalayas, across rivers, forests, and mountain roads. Some people complete it in one trip, others do it over time. Each stop has its own meaning, and the entire route is as much about the road as it is about the temples.<\/p><p data-start=\"2174\" data-end=\"2598\"><strong data-start=\"2174\" data-end=\"2191\">Hemkund Sahib<\/strong><br data-start=\"2191\" data-end=\"2194\" \/>Hemkund Sahib is a Sikh pilgrimage site set at high altitude near the Valley of Flowers. The trek is steep and the weather unpredictable, but the destination\u2014a gurudwara beside a glacial lake\u2014is worth it. It\u2019s peaceful, quiet, and full of respect. Many visit during the summer months when the snow melts and the path is open. It\u2019s a journey people take not just for religion, but for personal connection.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/details>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-aede31f e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"aede31f\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_parallax&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_backdrop&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_on_scroll&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_sticky&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is