pended&quot;:&quot;one&quot;,&quot;n_accordion_animation_duration&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;ms&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:400,&quot;sizes&quot;:[]},&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_sticky&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_scrollme&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_smoove&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_parallax_mouse&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_infinite&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_fadeout_animation&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_mobile_static&quot;:&quot;false&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"nested-accordion.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-n-accordion\" aria-label=\"Accordion. Open links with Enter or Space, close with Escape, and navigate with Arrow Keys\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<details id=\"e-n-accordion-item-2460\" class=\"e-n-accordion-item\" >\n\t\t\t\t<summary class=\"e-n-accordion-item-title\" data-accordion-index=\"1\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-controls=\"e-n-accordion-item-2460\" >\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-header'><div class=\"e-n-accordion-item-title-text\"> Read <span class=\"read-more\">More<\/span><span class=\"read-less\">Less<\/span> <\/div><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-icon'>\n\t\t\t<span class='e-opened' ><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"e-font-icon-svg e-fas-long-arrow-alt-down\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\"><path d=\"M168 345.941V44c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12h-56c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12v301.941H41.941c-21.382 0-32.09 25.851-16.971 40.971l86.059 86.059c9.373 9.373 24.569 9.373 33.941 0l86.059-86.059c15.119-15.119 4.411-40.971-16.971-40.971H168z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span>\n\t\t\t<span class='e-closed'><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"e-font-icon-svg e-fas-long-arrow-alt-right\" viewBox=\"0 0 448 512\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\"><path d=\"M313.941 216H12c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12v56c0 6.627 5.373 12 12 12h301.941v46.059c0 21.382 25.851 32.09 40.971 16.971l86.059-86.059c9.373-9.373 9.373-24.569 0-33.941l-86.059-86.059c-15.119-15.119-40.971-4.411-40.971 16.971V216z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span>\n\t\t<\/span>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/summary>\n\t\t\t\t<div role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"e-n-accordion-item-2460\" class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-933200c e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"933200c\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_parallax&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_backdrop&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_on_scroll&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_sticky&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_scrollme&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_smoove&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_parallax_mouse&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_infinite&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_fadeout_animation&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_mobile_static&quot;:&quot;false&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2d1bd4a elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2d1bd4a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_sticky&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_scrollme&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_smoove&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_parallax_mouse&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_infinite&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_fadeout_animation&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_mobile_static&quot;:&quot;false&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p data-start=\"504\" data-end=\"914\"><strong>Jim Corbett<\/strong> is one of the closest and most exciting options. It\u2019s around 6 to 7 hours from Delhi and ideal for families or nature lovers. Morning jeep safaris in zones like Bijrani or Dhikala offer chances to see tigers, elephants, and deer. The area around Dhikuli has nice riverside resorts and forest views. If you\u2019re going on a weekend, make sure to book your safari permits at least 10\u201315 days in advance.<\/p><p data-start=\"916\" data-end=\"1366\"><strong>Auli<\/strong> is a bit farther but perfect for snow lovers and peaceful views. It\u2019s best visited between December and February for snow, but even in summer it\u2019s quiet and scenic. You\u2019ll reach Joshimath first, and then take the famous cable car up to Auli. The views from the ropeway and the mountain stay options are totally worth the effort. If there\u2019s heavy snowfall, the road might close, so parking in Joshimath and riding the cable car is the safest bet.<\/p><p data-start=\"1368\" data-end=\"1768\"><strong>Rishikesh<\/strong> is always a solid weekend plan. Only 5\u20136 hours from Delhi, you get adventure, riverside stays, and a relaxed vibe all in one. Rafting from Shivpuri is popular between October and June, while yoga retreats and Ganga aarti at Triveni Ghat draw spiritual travelers year-round. Tapovan is the best area to stay if you want good caf\u00e9s, rafting access, and a bit of peace away from the main town.<\/p><p data-start=\"1770\" data-end=\"2144\"><strong>Nainital<\/strong> is great if you want something easy and scenic. It\u2019s around 7 hours away and works well for couples or families. You can walk along Mall Road, take a boat ride on Naini Lake, or go up to Snow View Point. If you stay slightly away from the lake\u2014say, Ayarpata Slopes\u2014you\u2019ll get better views and quieter surroundings, but still be close enough to explore town on foot.<\/p><p data-start=\"2146\" data-end=\"2478\"><strong>Mussoorie<\/strong> is another quick hill trip, just over 6 hours via Dehradun. It\u2019s perfect for mountain views, colonial caf\u00e9s, and short walks like Camel\u2019s Back Road or Lal Tibba. Families love the central locations, but Landour offers a more peaceful, boutique vibe. Try to avoid peak tourist weekends in May and June\u2014it gets crowded fast.<\/p><p data-start=\"2480\" data-end=\"2896\"><strong>Chopta<\/strong> is for travelers who like the mountains raw and real. It takes around 10\u201312 hours to reach, but once you&#8217;re there, it&#8217;s totally worth it. You\u2019ll find pine forests, snow in winter, and green meadows in summer. It\u2019s also the base for the Tungnath and Chandrashila trek, which is manageable even for beginners. Accommodation is limited and basic, so book early\u2014especially if you want a warm room and a good view.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/details>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6214f12 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"6214f12\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_parallax&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_backdrop&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_is_background_on_scroll&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_sidemenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_fullmenu&quot;:&quot;false&quot;,&quot;grandtour_ext_link_closed_fullmenu